article.description: Rachael Hencke scored 13 points to help Miami of Ohio beat No. 25 Bowling Green 45-40, ending the Falcons' 25-game winning streak Wednesday night.
article.headline: No. 25 Bowling Green has streak stopped by upstart Miami
article.story:
OXFORD, Ohio -- Rachael Hencke scored 13 points to help Miami of Ohio beat No. 25 Bowling Green 45-40, ending the Falcons' 25-game winning streak Wednesday night.

Tracy Pontius had 11 points for Bowling Green (25-3, 14-1 Mid-American), which earned its first ranking in two years Monday and hadn't lost since falling to Valparaiso in November. The Falcons winning streak was the second-longest in the country behind top-ranked UConn.

Trailing 34-32 with just under 4 minutes left, Miami (14-14, 6-9) went on a 10-0 run to take a 42-34 advantage. Stephanie Ford had a layup and two free throws during the spurt. Jenna Schone's jumper with 50 seconds left capped the burst.

Bowling Green closed to 43-40 with 8 seconds left, but Ashley Hawkins hit a pair of free throws to seal the win. The Falcons were just 12-for-60 (20 percent) from the field, including making just three of 25 3-pointers.

"Our players were prepared after coach Lisa Hayden's scouting report," Miami coach Maria Fantanarosa said. "We focused on Tracy Pontius and (Lauren) Prochaska and it changed BG's timing. Of course, they also had a night shooting 20 percent, so it all came together. Our defense kept us in the game and as it went on, it gave us a chance to win."

Bowling Green lost its first two games of the season before reeling off 25 straight victories. The Falcons scored the first five points of the game, holding Miami scoreless for over 7 minutes.

But the RedHawks answered with seven straight points during a span of 5:25 to open a two-point lead. Hencke scored five points during the run, including a three-point play that made the score 7-5.

Miami later trailed 10-7 with 4:32 left in the first half after another 5-0 run by the Falcons. It was 14-11 at the half.
